facts.fact: The article on Giganotosaurus was promoted to Featured Article status on November 19, 2016.
The nomination for Giganotosaurus was made by user FunkMonk on September 30, 2016.
Ian Rose processed the promotion of the Giganotosaurus article via FACBot.

sources.snippet: Baryonyx was a theropod dinosaur of the early Cretaceous Period "Period (geology)"), about 130–125 million years ago. An identifying specimen of the genus was discovered in 1983 in Surrey, England; fragmentary specimens were later discovered in other parts of the United Kingdom and Iberia. Meaning "heavy claw", Baryonyx refers to the animal's very large claw (31 cm or 12 in) on the first finger. The 1983 specimen is one of the most complete theropod skeletons from the UK, and its discovery attracted media attention. Baryonyx was about 7.5 m (25 ft) long and weighed 1.2 t (1.3 short tons).
